    • Constructor Detail

      • XmlAny

        public XmlAny(XmlDataWorkspace ws,
              int min,
              int max,
              java.lang.String process,
              java.lang.String... namespaces)
        Create an XmlAny item. This item can be used only as a member of an XmlSequence or XmlChoice model. Qualfiied names must be explicitly prefixed. There is no target namespace because a script may include more than one namespace.
        Parameters:
        ws - the XmlDaatWorkspace
        min - minOccurs
        max - maxOccurs
        process - String value of "strict", "skip", or "lax"
        namespaces - list of namespaces
        • when first namespace is ##any, no other names may be in the list.
        • when the first namespace is ##other, it may be followed by a single namespace that is the targetNamespace to be excluded; it would typically be the namespace of the parent complexType in order to achieve the ##other effect.
        • otherwise namespaces is treated like a list; it may include ##local Specifying ##targetNamespcae is not allowed because a script may define item in more than one namespace.
